verbs.description: fineer (third-person singular simple present fineers, present participle fineering, simple past and past participle fineered)
fineer (third-person singular simple present fineers, present participle fineering, simple past and past participle fineered)

entries.meaning: (intransitive, archaic) To acquire goods fraudulently by having them specially made so as to be unsuitable for other customers, and then threatening not to take them except on credit.
